name association-matrix
category Package
revision 76924
shortdesc LaTeX support for creating association matrices
longdesc This package allows the creation of association matrices in an
longdesc clear and concise fashion, without having to deal with manually
longdesc generating and modifying the tables while working. All you have
longdesc to do is define the rows and the columns by their unique
longdesc identifier, and then specify which cells should be marked as
longdesc associated. Then, the \amxgenerate command generates a table
longdesc that shows in the cells with a blip (*) where the association
longdesc was added. The package depends on etoolbox, forloop, ifthen,
longdesc textcomp, and xparse.
